init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He knew he would be called back into action.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He knew that Obama would be the one to save the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The note is the first step in a long journey.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He grabbed his phone and dialed the number on the note.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: After a few seconds, the automated voice came back on the line.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Obama did not respond, and the phone hung up on him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He waited for a few moments, and then the phone rang.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Obama hung up the phone and walked to the back door of his house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He opened the door and let JFK in.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Obama and JFK walked out of the house and got into JFK's car.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK started the car and drove off.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I know you've been waiting for this day for a long time.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "We're going to need to blow that up."
